2026-04-16T05:27:31.431Z JOY-00EE-58 comment.added "Fix landed: identity::resolve_identity now emits a clear stderr warning when JOY_SESSION is a live AI session for a different project than the current one. The warning names both the session's project/member and the current project, and points to 'joy auth token add <ai-member>' as the fix. Fallback to git-email identity unchanged so read-only commands still work. Pure helper cross_project_session_warning is unit-tested (236 joy-core tests, 163/163 BATS). Smoke-tested by running joy add in a neighbour project with a stale JOY_SESSION - warning prints, guard then denies." [ai:claude@joy delegated-by:horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
